  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba \u0d85\u0daf \u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db6\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Budget to the House today",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Budget Appropriation Amendment Bill (Budget Speech) will be presented to the Parliament by President Ranil Wickramasinghe today (30) afternoon.",
        "Parliament is scheduled to meet today (30) at 1.00 pm under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena.",
        "The President is scheduled to start reading the budget speech at around 1.00 pm.",
        "The Budget Appropriation Amendment Bill was presented to Parliament by Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena recently.",
        "According to the new amendment bill, the government expenditure will increase by about forty seven thousand crore rupees compared to last year."
      ],
